msgstr "Del capital a la credibilidad"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:101
msgid ""
"Prediction markets are one of the most powerful tools for measuring "
"collective intelligence — turning opinions into signals and future events "
"into public records."
msgstr ""
"Los mercados de predicción son una de las herramientas más poderosas para "
"medir la inteligencia colectiva, convirtiendo las opiniones en señales y los "
"eventos futuros en registros públicos."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:109
msgid "What gets measured"
msgstr "Qué se mide"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:115
msgid "Capital"
msgstr "Capital"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:121
msgid "Credibility"
msgstr "Credibilidad"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:132
msgid "Profit leaderboard — rewards bankrolls, not necessarily insight."
msgstr "Ranking de ganancias: premia bankrolls, no necesariamente criterio."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:148
msgid "Judgment leaderboard — earned through resolved forecasts."
msgstr "Ranking de criterio: se gana con pronósticos resueltos."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:166
msgid "The idea"
msgstr "La idea"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:171
msgid ""
"Credibility earned through a public history of judgment — not luck, not "
"capital, not hype. PredictStamp secures social intelligence with track "
"record."
msgstr ""
"Credibilidad ganada con un historial público de criterio — no suerte, ni "
"capital, ni hype. PredictStamp respalda la inteligencia social con historial."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:180
msgid "Secures with track record"
msgstr "Respaldado por historial"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:182
msgid ""
"You prove you built something real — thoughtful predictions, reasoning, "
"accuracy, and consistency over time. Every forecast, thesis, and challenge "
"adds to a public record that follows you."
msgstr ""
"Demuestras que construiste algo real: predicciones reflexivas, razonamiento, "
"precisión y consistencia a lo largo del tiempo. Cada pronóstico, tesis y "
"desafío se suma a un registro público que te sigue."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:185
msgid "Judgment is the entry fee"
msgstr "El criterio es la entrada"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:202 templates/dashboard/about.html:224
#: templates/dashboard/about.html:246
msgid "Tap to explore"
msgstr "Toca para explorar"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:209
msgid ""
"Formal forecasts tied to real markets — with confidence, reasoning, and "
"probability snapshots captured at the moment you call it."
msgstr ""
"Pronósticos formales vinculados a mercados reales, con instantáneas de "
"confianza, razonamiento y probabilidad capturadas en el momento en que lo "
"llamas."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:223
msgid "Resolution"
msgstr "Resolución"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:231
msgid ""
"Markets resolve objectively. Reputation follows accuracy — rewarding early "
"conviction against the odds and penalizing overconfidence."
msgstr ""
"Los mercados se resuelven objetivamente. La reputación sigue a la precisión, "
"recompensando la convicción temprana contra viento y marea y penalizando el "
"exceso de confianza."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:245
msgid "Verifiable history"
msgstr "Historial verificable"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:253
msgid ""
"Every prediction, comment, thesis, and challenge becomes durable history — "
"transparent, inspectable, and hard to rewrite after the fact."
msgstr ""
"Cada predicción, comentario, tesis y desafío se convierte en una historia "
"duradera: transparente, inspeccionable y difícil de reescribir después de "
"los hechos."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:261
msgid ""
"With <a href=\"https://attest.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener "
"noreferrer\" class=\"font-medium text-violet-600 underline decoration-"
"violet-300 underline-offset-2 hover:text-violet-700 dark:text-"
"violet-400\">EAS</a>, reputation can become portable, transparent, and hard "
"to fake — proofs you carry into other apps and agent ecosystems."
msgstr ""
"Con <a href=\"https://attest.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener "
"noreferrer\" class=\"font-medium text-violet-600 underline decoration-"
"violet-300 underline-offset-2 hover:text-violet-700 dark:text-"
"violet-400\">EAS</a>, la reputación puede volverse portátil, transparente y "
"difícil de falsificar, pruebas que llevas a otras aplicaciones y ecosistemas "
"de agentes."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:268
msgid "The platform"
msgstr "La plataforma"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:270
msgid "A social network for markets"
msgstr "Una red social para mercados"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:273
msgid ""
"<strong class=\"text-slate-800 dark:text-white\">PredictStamp</strong> is "
"built around events and outcomes — follow markets, publish theses, debate "
"probabilities, challenge friends, and build a public history of judgment."
msgstr ""
"<strong class=\"text-slate-800 dark:text-white\">PredictStamp</strong> se "
"basa en eventos y resultados — sigue mercados, publica tesis, debate "
"probabilidades, desafía amigos y construye un historial público de criterio."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:278
msgid "Domains and topics:"
msgstr "Dominios y temas:"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:280
msgid "Geopolitics"
msgstr "Geopolítica"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:283
msgid "Elections"
msgstr "Elecciones"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:284
msgid "Macro"
msgstr "Macro"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:285
msgid "Energy"
msgstr "Energía"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:286
msgid "Tech"
msgstr "Tecnología"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:287
msgid "Culture"
msgstr "Cultura"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:290
msgid ""
"A living map of who has good judgment — by specialty, not one blended score."
msgstr ""
"Un mapa vivo de quién tiene buen juicio — por especialidad, no un número "
"global mezclado."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:296
msgid "What we track"
msgstr "Qué registramos"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:298
msgid ""
"Every forecast captures more than yes or no — context that compounds into "
"reputation."
msgstr ""
"Cada pronóstico captura más que un sí o un no — contexto que se acumula en "
"reputación."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:306
msgid "Why do you believe this?"
msgstr "¿Por qué crees esto?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:312
msgid "How confident are you?"
msgstr "¿Qué tan seguro estás?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:318
msgid "Did you change your mind?"
msgstr "¿Cambiaste de opinión?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:324
msgid "Were you early or late?"
msgstr "¿Llegaste temprano o tarde?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:330
msgid "Did your reasoning age well?"
msgstr "¿Tu razonamiento envejeció bien?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:336
msgid "Are you right in this domain?"
msgstr "¿Acertás en este dominio?"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:346
msgid "Reputation vs Popularity"
msgstr "Reputación vs. Popularidad"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:349
msgid ""
"The platform records both popularity and reputation for every user. They "
"stay independent: popularity measures attention; reputation measures "
"demonstrated judgment."
msgstr ""
"La plataforma registra popularidad y reputación para cada usuario. Siguen "
"siendo independientes: la popularidad mide la atención; la reputación, el "
"criterio demostrado."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:378
msgid "Demonstrated judgment"
msgstr "Criterio demostrado"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:380
msgid ""
"Earned when forecasts resolve. Harder contrarian calls score higher. Upvotes "
"never touch this score."
msgstr ""
"Se gana cuando los pronósticos se resuelven. Las predicciones a "
"contracorriente más difíciles suman más. Los votos a favor no afectan esta "
"puntuación."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:394
msgid "Attention"
msgstr "Atención"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:396
msgid ""
"Driven by votes on comments and forecasts. A post can be popular and wrong — "
"memes welcome, but status comes from being right over time."
msgstr ""
"Impulsado por votos en comentarios y pronósticos. Una publicación puede ser "
"popular e incorrecta: los memes son bienvenidos, pero el estatus proviene de "
"tener razón con el tiempo."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:408
msgid "Meritocracy"
msgstr "Meritocracia"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:410
msgid "Leaderboards without betting"
msgstr "Rankings sin apuestas"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:413
msgid "Who has the best judgment? Not who made the most money."
msgstr "¿Quién tiene el mejor juicio? No quién hizo más dinero."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:419
msgid "Money"
msgstr "Dinero"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:430
msgid "Judgment"
msgstr "Criterio"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:459
msgid "Compete without betting"
msgstr "Compite sin apostar"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:462
msgid ""
"Challenge friends on real markets — private leaderboards and contests for "
"reputation, not money."
msgstr ""
"Desafía a tus amigos en mercados reales — rankings privados y concursos por "
"reputación, no por dinero."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:470
msgid "Challenges between friends"
msgstr "Desafíos entre amigos"

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:472
msgid ""
"Who gets more World Cup predictions right? Who wins on crypto this month? "
"Private leaderboards, topic-specific contests, time-limited or ongoing — "
"status without gambling."
msgstr ""
"¿Quién acierta más en las predicciones de la Copa del Mundo? ¿Quién gana en "
"criptomonedas este mes? Rankings privados, concursos de temas específicos, "
"de tiempo limitado o en curso: estado sin juegos de azar."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:475
msgid ""
"Fantasy sports × Reddit × prediction markets — based on reputation, not "
"betting."
msgstr ""
"Fantasy deportes × Reddit × mercados de predicción — por reputación, no por "
"apuestas."

#: templates/dashboard/about.html:478
msgid "Browse challenges"
msgstr "Ver desafíos"

